  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Head of Operations",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a Head of Operations to oversee and optimise the daily operations of businesses comprising a creative studio, cafe operations, and multiple technology-driven initiatives. This role is responsible for ensuring operational excellence, process efficiency, and the successful execution of innovation-led projects across the organisation.<br /></p><p>The role requires a candidate with strong operational leadership, cross-functional coordination skills, and the ability to manage complex workflows involving technology, vendors, and internal stakeholders.<br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>•\tLead and manage end-to-end business operations across studio, cafe, and digital initiatives to ensure efficiency, consistency, and scalability.</p><p>•\tDevelop, implement, and continuously improve operational processes, standard operating procedures (SOPs), and internal controls.</p><p>•\tOversee technology-enabled projects, including digital tools, workflow automation, operational systems, and external technology vendors.</p><p>•\tCoordinate and prioritise multiple concurrent projects, ensuring timelines, budgets, and deliverables are met.</p><p>•\tManage relationships with third-party service providers, suppliers, and technology partners, including contract oversight and performance evaluation.</p><p>•\tMonitor operational performance using key metrics, prepare management reports, and provide data-driven recommendations to leadership.</p><p>•\tSupport business innovation by translating new ideas into executable operational plans, pilot initiatives, and scalable systems.</p><p>•\tEnsure compliance with relevant regulatory, safety, and operational requirements applicable to café and studio operations.</p><p>•\tSupervise and guide operational staff where applicable, including scheduling, performance management, and skills development.</p><p></p><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><p>•\tDiploma or Degree in Business Administration, Operations Management, Information Systems, Hospitality Management, or a related field.</p><p>•\tDemonstrated experience managing business processes, operational systems, and cross-functional projects.</p><p>•\tStrong understanding of digital tools, operational software, or technology platforms used to improve business efficiency.</p><p>•\tProven ability to work independently, manage priorities, and solve operational problems in a fast-paced environment.</p><p>•\tStrong communication and stakeholder management skills.</p><p>•\tExperience in hospitality, creative industries, or small-to-medium enterprises is an advantage.</p>",
